    "Evaluator-1) the quality of all the engines is almost the same.",
    "The more proficient and knowledgeable the reviewer is, the higher is the difference in their ratings.",
    "We list sampled error analyses on the outputs from the finetuned WMT21fb and NLLB models in Figures 9-11 for the three tasks on translations of sentences, terms, and concepts.",
    "The preferred translations are highlighted in green colour and \"both sounds ok\" is marked in orange.",
    "From the comparisons of sampled output sentences, we discovered that the most frequent errors in a fine-grained analysis include literal translations, oral vs written languages, translation inconsistency, inaccuracy of terms, hallucination/madeup words, and gender-related errors such as feminine vs masculine, in addition to the standard fluency and adequacy that have been commonly used by traditional MT researchers (64)."
